lowest : Didn't know how to note this above, but I did step 1 anki for the entirety of my last clerkship then spent 2 weeks of dedicated studying                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              Focus more on the things that overlap with step 2                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     I could have studied less (like 3-4 weeks) because I was consistently scoring well enough to pass on my practice tests but I was too nervous to take any chances and decided to instead just use the entire 5 weeks I had already decided to allocate                                                                                                                                                 I did it in 3 weeks and it was VERY stressful. However, this ended up being more than enough time. I would feel reassured that again it is PASS/FAIL so it will be OK!!                                                                                                                                                                                                                               I ended up taking 12 weeks. M1 was terrible for me and I didn't know how to study. So, I would go back and study more for it during M1 or M2 but even 12 weeks was pushing it for me to make up the deficit I was in                                                                                                                                                                                 
highest: Taking a longer period of time for dedicated. Not done anything else but study during those months                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Though I probably could have studied much less, I did not find the '% likelihood of passing' metric very reassuring and still ended up studying a lot of make sure it was as reassuring as possible.                                                                                                                                                                                                  Use less time. 4-5 weeks is good enough.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                              would have done more sketchy, moved through pathoma faster (knew most of it already from shelf exams/clinical year)                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Would have started earlier in preclinical - would have ignored my preclinical classes and used more outside resources to build foundation. It was difficult to get up to speed for Step 1, and I regret not studying more in preclinical as I think my Step 2 score would have been significantly higher. I feel that what was not discussed was how much Step 1 content is still relevant to Step 2.

I still stressed out more than I needed to though and had to remind myself about the Pass/Fail mindset.                                                                                                                                                   Honestly, studying for Step 1 after taking Step 2 was quite easy. The vast majority of the knowledge is already there, you just need to supplement with the concepts that aren't as clinically relevant + become adjusted to the way Step 1 questions are asked. I was somewhat burnt out after studying for Step 2 and feel like my Step 1 studying was not as efficient and I already had strongly passing scores, so I could've studied less.  I felt mostly prepared for this from Step 2 studying given that I put a lot of focus on pathophysiology. I wish I would have taken this first, though, to have more basic science context for Step 2 that I think would have gotten me some more points.

lowest : *correction above: I remember the NBME form it was NBME14 which wasn't listed as an option on the drop down menu                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                          6 weeks is an appropriate time. Highly recommend anki.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    As I noted before, would definitely have studied more preclinical year, as it would have helped my shelf exam and thus my step 2 scores. I also would have done fewer UWorld questions, more AMBOSS questions, and also done the questions more slowly. I was rushing to finish UWorld which was overly straightforward compared to the real exam.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                        Dedicated time exclusive to step 2 post clerkship with step 1 completed pre-clerkship.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Everyone studies differently, but for me I would have done more studying outside of my dedicated time. I sort of did that already with shelf exams over my third year of medical school, but more acutely I would have liked to have done uworld then finished amboss, as well as use the Anking deck more regularly the 2 months prior to my step 2 dedicated. If I had had the time, I would have also reviewed the practice shelf exams I took on NBME. I don't think this is all necessary for the average student studying for step, depending on their goal score range, but that's what I would change for myself.
highest: Studied more for Step 1. Would have done Anki in the months leading up to the exam.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Take it when I was ready to vs when I was advised to since I was burnt out by the exam day.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               Try to do more timed Uworld outside of practice exams. The hardest part of the real test was working through questions quickly enough. Timing my Uworld also would have helped me get through a larger % of the uworld questions.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         Use anki more for understanding concepts than memorizing amboss/uworld questions. Make cards with better info                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             Wish I had an easier rotation the month before my 4 week protected study block so that I could have eased into studying and started questions ahead of time.
